LINKING : 

    CHECK LINKS INODE NUMBER : ls -i

    CREATE HARD LINK : ln /Path/To/File LinkName

    CREATE SOFT LINK : ln -s /Path/To/File LinkName

    REMOVE LINK : unlink LinkName


ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES : 

    LIST ALL ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES : env OR printenv

    GET VALUE OF ENVIRONMENT VARIABLE : echo $VARIABLE_NAME

    CREATE A LOCAL ENVIRONMENT VARIABLE : VARIABLE_NAME='Value'

    ADD LOCAL ENVIRONMENT VARIABLE : export VARIABLE_NAME='Value'

    SEE PATH ENVIRONMENT VARIABLE : echo $PATH

    ADD PATH VALUE : PATH="$PATH:/Path/To/Script/File "

    PERMANENT ENVIRONMENT VARIABLE FOR A USER : 

        FILE LOCATION : ls -la ~/.profile OR ~/.bashrc

        ADD LINES : export VARIABLES_NAME="Variable_Value"

        UPDATE FILE CHANGES : source ~/.profile

    PERMANENT ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES FOR ALL USERS : 

        FILE LOCATION : ls -la /etc/profile

        ADD LINES : export VARIABLES_NAME="Variable_Value"

        UPDATE FILE CHANGES : source /etc/profile


DF : 

    SEE DISK FILE SYSTEM : df

    SEE FILE SYSTEM WITH TYPE : df -T

    SHOW TOTAL IN LAST LINE : df --total OR du -c

    EXCLUDE TMPFS FILE SYSTEM : df -x tmpfs

    SEE INODES WITH FILE SYSTEM : df -i


DU : 

    SEE SUBDIRECTORIES AND DIRECTORY USAGE : du /Path/To/Files/Folders

    SEE FOR ALL : du -a OR df -a

    SUMMARIZES USAGE BY DIRECTORY : du -s /Path/

    USE NCDU : ncdu


FREE : 

    CHECK RAM AND SWAP : free

    ADD TOTAL IN LAST : free --total

    REFRESH EVERY N SECONDS : free -s N

    REFRESH EVERY M TILL N TIMES  : free -s M -c N 


DD : 

    COPY ONE FILE TO OTHER : dd if=/Path/inputfile of=/Path/outputfile

    COPY EACH BLOCKSIZE AT A TIME : dd if=/Path/inputfile of=/Path/outputfile bs=N

    COPY M NUMBER OF CHARACTORS ONLY WITH BLOCKSIZE N : dd if=/Path/inputfile of=/Path/outputfile bs=N count=M

    SKIP X NUMBER OF CHARACTORS WHILE COPY : dd if=/Path/inputfile of=/Path/outputfile bs=N skip=8


TYPES : 

    FILE : -
    DIRECTORY : d
    LINK : l
    DEVICE FILE : c
    SOCKET : s
    FIFO OR NAMED FILE : p
    BLOCK DEVICE : d


DMESG : 

    DISPLAY KERNAL RELATED MESSAGES FROM KERNAL RING BUFFER : dmesg 

    DISPLAY IN HUMAN READABLE DECODED FORMAT WITH TIMESTAMP : dmesg -HTx

    LIVE MONITORING :dmesg -w

    CLEAR RING BUFFER : dmesg -c


LOGS : 

    LOCATION : /var/log

    LOGROTATE : 

        CONFIG FILE AND DIRECTORY : /etc/logrotate.conf

        WRITE LOG ROTATE SCRIPT UNDER THIS FOLDER : /etc/logrotate.d/

        CHECK LOGROTATE STATUS AND TRIGGER TIME : sudo systemctl status logrotate.timer

        TRIGGER INSTANTLY : logrotate /var/log/logrotate.d/ScriptName

        CHECK DEBUG : logrotate -d /var/log/logrotate.d/ScriptName
    
